hi @candacejohnsonbakerlab the second error is expected; on MacOS you can't launch from ipython, as it's not a framework build of python. You will need to run `pythonw -m deeplabcut` directly from the terminal. Your conda env has wxpython, so it should all work, very strange -- can you post the full output of your terminal when you run `pythonw -m deeplabcut`

Thanks for getting back to me! This is what I receive when I run that command


(DEEPLABCUT) candacejohnson@river ~ % pythonw -m deeplabcut
/System/Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/2.7/Resources/Python.app/Contents/MacOS/Python: No module named deeplabcut
(DEEPLABCUT) candacejohnson@river ~ % pythonw -m DEEPLABCUT
/System/Library/Frameworks/Python.framework/Versions/2.7/Resources/Python.app/Contents/MacOS/Python: No module named DEEPLABCUT

For some reasons, `pythonw` is linked to python 2.7 and not to the one in your environment. Users had found the solution to this very problem [here](https://github.com/DeepLabCut/DeepLabCut/issues/1218#issuecomment-853280085). It should work fine afterwards ☺️.
yep! just need to be sure to use python3, so activate env, and run `conda install python.app`
